The exponential-power function is less intuitive, and deserves further consideration. At the outset, it should be noted that the square root of time that is used in this function reflects a setting of the exponent of the power function of this formula to .5 (after Wickelgren, 1974). The more expanded version has an additional parameter: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
